I"b<p>I’ve spent the last seven years studying pathogen transmission. I studied how <em>Mycobacterium bovis</em>, a bacteria that causes bovine tuberculosis, is transmitted between cattle and wildlife.</p>

<p>I am excited to be starting a new job as a Data Scientist. I’ll be using loads of new data sources, like satellite imagery, phone records, or social media data to help aid operations around the world.</p>

<p>I have a passion for Data Science, teaching and science communication. I also love sport and being outside.</p>

<p>Joanna and I have just moved back to Glasgow, where we both studied for almost ten years, and we’re excited to settle back into life here with our new baby (Aven)!</p>

